cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with the problem of 3D object detection from monocular images, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end deep learning architecture, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem of 3D object detection also has applications in robotics, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes a new feature transformation technique, which involves reasoning about the spatial configuration of the scene, and this falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing to some extent, as it involves interpreting the abstract and the title of the paper, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
